sentences: After studying with Paul Hindemith and Arnold Schering in Berlin, he taught as a professor at the Franz Liszt Academy of Music in Budapest from 1941 until 1967.
After studying with Paul Hindemith and Arnold Schering in Berlin, he taught as a professor at the Franz Liszt Academy of Music in Budapest from 1941 until 1967.
He also led the faculty for Protestant sacred music until it was closed by the communists in 1949.
Gárdonyi lived in Germany with his family beginning in 1972.

sentences: Zoltán Gárdonyi (Hungarian pronunciation: [ˈzoltaːn ˈɡaːrdoɲi]; 25 April 1906 – 27 June 1986) was a Hungarian composer and musicologist.
He taught at the Franz Liszt Academy of Music for 26 years.
He died in Westfalian Herford a few weeks after his 80th birthday.
